"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-07-22-olympics-running-track-painted-purple-paris-2024-21273224\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"The running track at the 2024Olympic GamesinParishas been painted purple in a very bold move - and fans are keen to know why.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 125, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Thefirst Olympic eventsget underway in the French capital on Wednesday and Thursday this week, before the official opening ceremony takes place on Friday.\", \"from\": 127, \"to\": 281, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 170, \"end\": 176, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.8391890207668625, \"rank\": 0.15234947017980646, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some of the upcoming athletic events will take place on a rare purple running track - a colour which has never been used before, according to the Olympic website.\", \"from\": 283, \"to\": 445, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was a 'long process' forParis 2024organisers to get it set up.\", \"from\": 447, \"to\": 512, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But why have they decided to paint the track purple?\", \"from\": 513, \"to\": 565, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read on to find out\\u2026  Alain Blondel, the sports manager in charge of athletics for Paris 2024, has explained two key reasons why such an unusual decision was made.\", \"from\": 566, \"to\": 729, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 588, \"end\": 601, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alain_Blondel\", \"score\": 0.9999990810651654, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alain Blondel\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alain_Blondel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alain_Blondel\"}, {\"begin\": 649, \"end\": 659, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 3.8192597979605117e-13, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The first is that Paris 2024 organisers firmly wanted something 'outside the box' - likely to get people talking and build interest - witha huge number of tickets still unsold.\", \"from\": 731, \"to\": 907, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 749, \"end\": 759, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 3.8192597979605117e-13, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0094\\u009c\\u00f0\\u009f\\u008f\\u0083\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0093\\u00b9:@Paris2024pic.twitter.com/rUhlI4luKS  'The big part of the job was to come up with a track that was different from what we had seen,' Blondel said.\", \"from\": 909, \"to\": 1069, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'[In order] to maintain the creative approach that the Organising Committee has had since it was set up, to go a little bit outside the box.'\", \"from\": 1071, \"to\": 1212, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The second reason is because the colour is said to 'highlight' athletes who will be competing on the track.\", \"from\": 1214, \"to\": 1321, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Blondel also explained the turns at the end of the bend are grey in tribute to the ash-coloured tracks\\u00a0at the Paris Games back in 1924.\", \"from\": 1323, \"to\": 1458, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'The look of the Games includes three colours for all the competition venues: blue, green and purple,' he added.\", \"from\": 1460, \"to\": 1572, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris Olympics gets underway onWednesday, July 24, 2024with the opening ceremony taking place on Friday, July 26, 2024.\", \"from\": 1574, \"to\": 1697, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The closing ceremony is on Sunday, August 11, 2024.\", \"from\": 1698, \"to\": 1749, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's not only the purple running track that's got people talking, there are also a number of bizarre rules at the Games, such as:  Wrestlers must carry a handkerchief- Olympic wrestlers must carry a hanky, known as a \\\"bloodrag,\\\" somewhere in their uniform.\", \"from\": 1751, \"to\": 2007, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's used to clean up any bleeding during the competition.\", \"from\": 2008, \"to\": 2066, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Boxers must be clean shaven- Competitors in the boxing competition must be clean-shaven or have very limited facial hair.\", \"from\": 2068, \"to\": 2189, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Boxers must be clean shaven to ensure cuts and injuries are easily visible for prompt medical attention and to reduce the risk of abrasions.\", \"from\": 2190, \"to\": 2330, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A pencil mustache, however, is allowed.\", \"from\": 2331, \"to\": 2370, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Clean hair only for Karate competitors- Make sure to lather up that shampoo, because karate referees have the authority to disqualify an athlete if they judge their hair to be insufficiently clean.\", \"from\": 2372, \"to\": 2569, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2392, \"end\": 2398, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karate\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.029153238091598e-17, \"text\": \"Karate\", \"types\": [\"Q349\", \"Q1914636\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karate\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karate\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Clean hair also reduces the risk of transmitting infections and diseases during close-contact combat.\", \"from\": 2570, \"to\": 2671, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"No groin grabbing in Water Polo- Water polo is a physically demanding sport, but excessive force, including groin grabbing, is strictly prohibited.\", \"from\": 2673, \"to\": 2820, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Cyclists' socks can only go to mid-calf- In Olympic cycling, there is an unusual uniform rule: socks cannot extend beyond mid-calf length and are subject to measurement, this is in place to maintain fair competition and aerodynamic consistency.\", \"from\": 2822, \"to\": 3066, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Longer socks could provide an aerodynamic advantage by reducing drag, and regulating sock length ensures all cyclists compete under the same conditions.\", \"from\": 3067, \"to\": 3219, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'We decided on this purple track with different tones: lighter for the track, darker for the service areas, and grey for the turns at the end of the bend, reminding of the ash-coloured tracks that were there 100 years ago for the Olympic Games Paris 1924.\", \"from\": 3221, \"to\": 3476, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'We had to work hard on the colours, so that they came out in the best possible tones to highlight the athletes.\", \"from\": 3478, \"to\": 3590, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'It's a track, it has to be pretty, but above all it's a stage on which the athletes are going to perform.\", \"from\": 3592, \"to\": 3698, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"What's really important is that the colours and the athletes stand out.'\", \"from\": 3699, \"to\": 3771, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ArrowMORE:Tom Daley among Olympians debunking 'anti-sex beds' myth at Paris 2024  ArrowMORE:Is Andy Murray retiring after the Olympic tennis tournament in Paris?\", \"from\": 3773, \"to\": 3934, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3783, \"end\": 3792, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Daley\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.442389142984617e-26, \"text\": \"Tom Daley\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Daley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Daley\"}, {\"begin\": 3